text:
Manufacturing process of a positioning control tool via 3d-printing technology

This invention is relative to a manufacturing process of a positioning control tool via 3D-printing technology comprising a set of steps such as: 
- 3D-print (400) with a polymer material mixed with powdered graphene (12a), a plurality of features (410) on a substrate (205), said features (410) comprising: 
- a resonator (411) transducer for creating a first surface acoustic wave (215); 
- a pair of reflectors (412a, 412b) for reflecting said first surface acoustic wave (215); 
- a structure (413), wherein a Coriolis force acting upon said structure (413) creates a second surface acoustic wave (230); and 
- a first sensor transducer (414) for sensing said second surface acoustic wave (230); and 
- a second sensor transducer (415) for sensing a residual surface acoustic wave from the second region of said surface (210) that is free of any structure that said Coriolis force is able to act upon;

Method and system for providing energy services
The present document relates to a system for providing energy services in an energy grid (110) using a cloud environment (120) comprising a distributed server architecture for processing computational tasks and a plurality of storage entities (124) for storing information, the system further comprising: 
- at least one control entity (130) being adapted to receive information from at least one of a plurality of energy grid elements (150) and operate the energy grid elements (150) based on operational policies (160); 
- one or more control interfaces (140) being coupled with the energy grid elements (150), the control interfaces (140) being adapted to transmit information provided by an energy grid element (150) to a control entity (130) and/or the control interfaces (140) being adapted to receive information from the control entity (130) in order to operate the energy grid element (150) based on said information; 

wherein the at least one control entity (130) comprises a plurality of software modules which are hosted in said cloud environment (120) and said operational 
policies (160) are stored in storage entities (124) of said cloud environment (120) in order to operate the energy grid elements (150) according to said operational policies (160).

Method for centring and dimensioning an image on a cathode-ray tube
The steps of the process comprise:  
     (a) measuring ( 50 ) the durations (T1 HAV , T2 HAV ) of the vertical black edges of the image and modifying step by step the adjustment (HPOS) for horizontal centering to obtain equal lateral vertical edges;  
     (b) measuring ( 52 ) the durations (T1 HAV  and T2 HAV ) of the vertical black edges of the image to calculate the adjustment (HSIZE) of the horizontal dimension of the image so as to cause the vertical black edges to disappear;  
     (c) measuring ( 54 ) the durations (T1 VAV  and T2 VAV ) of the horizontal black edges of the image to calculate the adjustment of the vertical dimension of the image (VSIZE′) and the adjustment of the vertical centering of the image (VPOS′) so as to cause the horizontal black edges to disappear and to center the image vertically, and  
     (d) recording ( 56 ) the adjustment values obtained (HPOS, HSIZE, VSIZE′ and VPOS′) in a memory of the display calculator.
